<paragraph blockId="39.[136,1452,373,544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,410,436]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Notes:—</emphasis>
For years, this proliferous species remained unnoticed and misidentify as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ames" authorityYear="1923" box="[1092,1230,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1092,1230,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only previously known proliferous species reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[583,710,446,472]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" box="[722,967,446,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis box="[722,967,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Myoxanthus sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by linear leaves and flowers with brownish sepals, yellowish translucent petals and yellow lip. The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" box="[1199,1363,483,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panamense">
<emphasis box="[1199,1363,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. panamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the former by the brownish sepals 
<emphasis box="[873,896,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. greenish translucent and yellow lip 
<emphasis box="[1310,1333,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. purple.
</paragraph>
